[For years veterinarians have known that diseases passed from people to
their animals. Many times veterinarians have seen the family pet brought in
for what appeared to be a cold, only to learn that family members had had
the cold a few weeks before. This is minor compared with MRSA, but issues
of diseases transmitting between species is not a one way street. It is
gratifying to veterinarians to have researchers prove that at least one
disease is transmitted both ways. - Mod.TG]
